Variable.Name: vl_MAIL_GROUP
Variable.Description: Used to email the error message from the Powershell script that parses the MANUAL_STANDARD_CONTRACT_QUOTES file for the correct Price Date.

Variable.Name: Script
Variable.Value:
<# .SYNOPSIS Script parses the STANDARD_CONTRACT_QUOTES file and verifies the PRICE_DATE equals the current Batch Date.
.DESCRIPTION This Powershell script verifies the MANUAL_STD_CONTRACT_QUOTES.csv file prior to running the MANUAL_QUOTE Batch Job Group that the PRICE_DATE from the file equals the current Batch Date.
.INPUTS CSV file
.OUTPUTS Boolean to proceed with script.
.NOTES Version: 1.0 Author: Steven Zussino Creation Date: 20220413 Purpose/Change: Initial script development
#>
#---------------------------------------------------------[Initializations]--------------------------------------------------------
Set-PSDebug -Trace 0
Set-StrictMode -Version Latest
#----------------------------------------------------------[Declarations]----------------------------------------------------------
# CSV data source $CSV_Data_Source = "${//@Trigger.Filename}";
$batch_date = "${vl_EFFECTIVE_DATE}";
#-----------------------------------------------------------[Execution]------------------------------------------------------------
######################################################################################## # Process the source file and verify the Price Date = Batch Date ########################################################################################
try { import-CSV -Path $CSV_Data_Source | ForEach {
$name = $_.NAME $price_date = $_.PRICE_DATE
if ($price_date -ne $batch_date) {
$Active_Batch_Output = $name + ' has a price date that is ' + $price_date + '. This does not match the Batch Date of: ' + $batch_date abatset /var "Output_Message = $name has a price date that is $price_date. This does not match the Batch Date of: $batch_date" Write-output $Active_Batch_Output Exit 1 }
}
} catch { abatset /var "Output_Message = 'Could not import the CSV file." Exit 1 }
try { $Active_Batch_Output = 'All the spreads price dates match the Batch Date of ' + $batch_date abatset /var "Output_Message = 'All the spreads price dates match the Batch Date of $batch_date" Write-output $Active_Batch_Output Exit 0 } catch { Exit 0 }

<ObjectBindingCollection xmlns:i="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns="http://schemas.activebatch.com/2008/10/01/ComponentModel"><ObjectBinding i:type="TextBinding"><Path>Script</Path><Value><#
.SYNOPSIS
  Script parses the STANDARD_CONTRACT_QUOTES file and verifies the PRICE_DATE equals the current Batch Date. 

.DESCRIPTION
  This Powershell script verifies the MANUAL_STD_CONTRACT_QUOTES.csv file prior to running the MANUAL_QUOTE Batch Job Group that the PRICE_DATE from the file equals the current Batch Date. 
  
.INPUTS
  CSV file  

.OUTPUTS 
  Boolean to proceed with script. 

.NOTES
  Version:        1.0
  Author:         Steven Zussino
  Creation Date:  20220413
  Purpose/Change: Initial script development

#>

#---------------------------------------------------------[Initializations]--------------------------------------------------------

Set-PSDebug -Trace 0

Set-StrictMode -Version Latest

#----------------------------------------------------------[Declarations]----------------------------------------------------------

# CSV data source
$CSV_Data_Source = "${//@Trigger.Filename}";

$batch_date = "${vl_EFFECTIVE_DATE}";

#-----------------------------------------------------------[Execution]------------------------------------------------------------

########################################################################################
# Process the source file and verify the Price Date = Batch Date
########################################################################################

try {
import-CSV -Path $CSV_Data_Source | ForEach {

  $name                = $_.NAME
  $price_date          = $_.PRICE_DATE

  if ($price_date -ne $batch_date) { 
  
    $Active_Batch_Output = $name + ' has a price date that is ' + $price_date + '. This does not match the Batch Date of: ' + $batch_date	    
	abatset /var "Output_Message = $name has a price date that is $price_date. This does not match the Batch Date of: $batch_date"
	Write-output $Active_Batch_Output
    Exit 1
  }

}

} catch {
  abatset /var "Output_Message = 'Could not import the CSV file."
  Exit 1
}

try {
  $Active_Batch_Output = 'All the spreads price dates match the Batch Date of ' + $batch_date	
  abatset /var "Output_Message = 'All the spreads price dates match the Batch Date of $batch_date"
  Write-output $Active_Batch_Output
  Exit 0
} catch {
  Exit 0
}</Value></ObjectBinding></ObjectBindingCollection>
